THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. A landlord of a covered premises shall establish:
4 (a) A policy requiring an applicant for employment with the landlord to
5 undergo a criminal background check as a condition of employment if the
6 position for which the applicant is applying entails access to any dwelling unit
7 key; and
8 (b) Written policies and procedures regarding the:
9 (1) Storage, issuance, return and security of dwelling unit keys; and
10 (2) If applicable, the usage and deactivation of dwelling unit keys.
11 2. A landlord of a covered premises shall maintain on the premises a log
12 that accounts for the issuance and return of each dwelling unit key and the
13 written policies and procedures established pursuant to paragraph (b) of
14 subsection 1.
15 3. In addition to any other remedies, if a landlord of a covered premises
16 violates this section, a person aggrieved by the violation or a district attorney may
17 bring a civil action in a court of competent jurisdiction against the landlord to
18 seek any or all of the following relief:
19 (a) Declaratory and injunctive relief.
20 (b) Actual damages.
21 (c) Reasonable attorney’s fees and costs.
22 (d) Any other legal or equitable relief that the court deems appropriate.
23 4. As used in this section:
24 (a) “Covered premises” means:
25 (1) In a county whose population is 100,000 or more, a premises
26 comprising more than 50 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property;
27 or
28 (2) In a county whose population is less than 100,000, a premises
29 comprising more than [10] 30 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of
30 property.
31 (b) “Dwelling unit key” means any physical or electronic mechanism used to
32 gain access to a dwelling unit, including, without limitation, a combination or
33 access code.
34 (c) “Financial institution” means any bank, savings and loan association,
35 savings bank, thrift company, credit union or financial institution that is licensed,
36 registered or otherwise authorized to do business in this State.
37 (d) “Landlord” does not include a financial institution, real estate broker,
38 real estate broker-salesperson or real estate salesperson.
39 (e) “Real estate broker” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 645.030.
40 (f) “Real estate broker-salesperson” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS
41 645.035.
42 (g) “Real estate salesperson” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 645.040.

